---

<BaseLayout>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <title>EVR:RDY — Command Brief for Critical Infrastructure Defense</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="One-page briefing on EVR:RDY’s TacSOC and T.A.P.S. pipeline securing critical infrastructure. See mission, pipeline flow, team, and partnership paths."
    />
    <meta property="og:title" content="EVR:RDY — Command Brief for Critical Infrastructure Defense" />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="Veteran-led operators delivering TacSOC and the T.A.P.S. telemetry pipeline. Mission, momentum, and partnership opportunities in one scroll."
    />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://evrrdy.com/" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://evrrdy.com/img/banner.png" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="EVR:RDY — Command Brief for Critical Infrastructure Defense" />
    <meta
      name="twitter:description"
      content="Veteran-led OT/ICS defense. Explore TacSOC and the T.A.P.S. pipeline milestones, team, and partnership paths."
    />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://evrrdy.com/img/banner.png" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://evrrdy.com/" />
    <script
      type="application/ld+json"
      set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "EVR:RDY Defensive Operations Group LLC",
      "url": "https://evrrdy.com/",
      "logo": "https://evrrdy.com/img/logo.png",
        "description": "Veteran-led operators delivering TacSOC and the T.A.P.S. telemetry pipeline for critical infrastructure."
      })}
    />
  </Fragment>

  <Header currentPath="/" />

  <main id="main-content" class="command-brief">
    <section id="mission" class="anchor-offset mission-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="split-layout">
          <article class="split-copy split-copy--framed split-copy--framed--mission" aria-label="Mission">
          <span class="hero-eyebrow">Veteran-led defensive operations</span>
          <h1>Defend Critical Infrastructure Without Compromise</h1>
          <p>
            EVR:RDY unites combat-tested defenders and civilian builders to deliver low-cost, practical protection for OT/ICS operators. This isn’t "just" a mission—it’s a
            mandate.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="mission-quote-secondary">
            We have done so much, for so long, with so little, we are now qualified to do anything with nothing.<br />
            <span>– Frank Sinatra</span>
        </blockquote>
        </article>
          <aside class="split-sidecards" aria-label="Challenge and solution">
          <article class="card hero-flagship-card">
            <div class="flagship-meta">
              <h2 class="challenge-title">Challenge</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="flagship-one-liner">OT operators must defend more with less:</p>
            <ul class="flagship-bullets challenge">
              <li>Underfunded programs can’t bankroll full-scale SOC buildouts or heavy appliances.</li>
              <li>Legacy platforms demand capex and licenses smaller utilities cannot sustain.</li>
              <li>Talent shortages make automation and pooled expertise mandatory.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="card hero-flagship-card">
            <div class="flagship-meta">
              <h2 class="solution-title">Solution</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="flagship-one-liner">Scaleable, lean defensive operations. Commodity telemetry pipelines—without the vendor tax.</p>
            <ul class="flagship-bullets solution">
              <li>Shrink analyst-to-asset ratios to enable accelerated response.</li>
              <li>Feed analytics with secure telemetry running on commodity hardware.</li>
              <li>Blend mentorship and speed with Veteran-led teams—operators defend forward.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
      </section>

    <section id="overview" class="split-section anchor-offset">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="split-layout">
          <article class="split-copy split-copy--framed split-copy--framed--overview" aria-label="Overview">
          <span class="hero-eyebrow">Affordable Critical Infrastructure Defense</span>
          <h1>Open-source OT/ICS defense you can actually afford.</h1>
          <p>
            EVR:RDY combines lean operations with commodity telemetry so resource-constrained operators can defend critical infrastructure without big-box price tags.
          </p>
        </article>
          <aside class="split-sidecards" aria-label="Flagship capabilities">
          {flagshipProducts.map((product) => (
            <article class="card hero-flagship-card">
              <div class="flagship-meta">
                <h3>{product.name}</h3>
                <span
                  class={`status-indicator ${product.variant === 'design' ? 'design' : product.variant === 'pilot' ? 'pilot' : ''}`}
                >
                  {product.status}
                </span>
              </div>
              <p class="flagship-one-liner">{product.oneLiner}</p>
              <ul class="flagship-bullets">
                {product.bullets.map((bullet) => (
                  <li>{bullet}</li>
                ))}
              </ul>
              <a class="flagship-link" href={product.link}>View {product.name}</a>
            </article>
          ))}
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
      </section>

    <section id="pipeline" class="anchor-offset">
      <div class="container">
          <article class="card pipeline-card">
            <span class="hero-eyebrow">Mission Data on Tap</span>
          <div class="pipeline-intro">
            <h2>Pipeline</h2>
            <p>
              The T.A.P.S. pipeline moves telemetry from the edge of an OT network into analysts’ hands. Each stage is transparent about status, funding needs, and
              mission impact.
            </p>
            <p>
              From SCOUT at the host to the TacSOC, every component is engineered to keep defenders ahead of threats without vendor lock-in.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pipeline-flow pipeline-flow--compact">
            {pipelineDomains.map((domain, domainIndex) => (
              <Fragment>
                <div class={`pipeline-domain ${domain.variant ?? ''}`} data-pipeline-domain={`${domain.id}-compact`}>
                  <header class="domain-header">
                    <span class="domain-badge">{domain.label}</span>
                    <div class="domain-meta">
                      <h4>{domain.title}</h4>
                      <span class={`status-indicator ${domain.statusVariant ?? ''}`}>{domain.status}</span>
          </div>
                  </header>
                  <p class="domain-summary">{domain.summary}</p>
                  <div class="domain-components domain-components--compact">
                    {domain.components.map((component, componentIndex) => (
                      <Fragment>
                        <details class={`component-compact ${component.components ? 'component-compact--group' : ''}`}>
                          <summary>
                            <span class="component-label">{component.name}</span>
                            {component.status ? (
                              <span class={`status-indicator ${component.variant ?? ''}`}>{component.status}</span>
                            ) : null}
                          </summary>
                          <div class="component-body">
                            {component.description ? <p>{component.description}</p> : null}
                            {component.components ? (
                              <div class="component-subgrid">
                                {component.components.map((subComponent) => (
                                  <div class={`component-subcard ${subComponent.variant ?? ''}`}>
                                    <div class="component-subcard-header">
                                      <span>{subComponent.name}</span>
                                      {subComponent.status ? (
                                        <span class={`status-indicator ${subComponent.variant ?? ''}`}>{subComponent.status}</span>
                                      ) : null}
          </div>
                                    {subComponent.description ? <p>{subComponent.description}</p> : null}
                                    {subComponent.outcome ? (
                                      <p class="component-impact"><strong>Impact:</strong> {subComponent.outcome}</p>
                                    ) : null}
        </div>
                                ))}
          </div>
                            ) : null}
                            {component.outcome ? (
                              <p class="component-impact"><strong>Impact:</strong> {component.outcome}</p>
                            ) : null}
          </div>
                        </details>
                        {componentIndex < domain.components.length - 1 ? (
                          <div class="connector-line connector-line--compact" aria-hidden="true">
                            <span class="pipeline-line"></span>
                            <span class="pipeline-arrow">↓</span>
                            <span class="pipeline-line"></span>
          </div>
                        ) : null}
                      </Fragment>
                    ))}
        </div>
                </div>
                {domainIndex < pipelineDomains.length - 1 ? (
                  <div class="compact-domain-connector" aria-hidden="true">
                    <span class="pipeline-line"></span>
                    <span class="pipeline-arrow">↓</span>
                    <span class="pipeline-line"></span>
                  </div>
                ) : null}
              </Fragment>
            ))}
          </div>
        </article>
        </div>
      </section>

    <section id="team" class="anchor-offset">
      <div class="container">
        <article class="team-panel split-copy--framed split-copy--framed--team">
          <header class="team-panel-header">
              <span class="hero-eyebrow">Veterans Running Point</span>
              <h2>The EVR:RDY Team</h2>
            <p>
              Veteran responders build the TacSOC and T.A.P.S. pipeline so critical infrastructure stays defended. Expand any bio to see the depth behind the mission and
              the blend of mission-first leadership with engineering rigor.
            </p>
          </header>
          <div class="team-stack">
            {teamMembers.map((member) => (
              <article class="team-card team-card--stacked">
                <div class="team-header">
                  <div class="team-avatar">
                    <img src={member.photo} alt={member.name} class="team-photo" loading="lazy" />
                    <div class="team-link-icons">
                      {member.linkedin ? (
                        <a class="team-link-icon" href={member.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label={`LinkedIn profile for ${member.name}`}>
                          <svg class="icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="img" aria-hidden="true">
                            <path d="M4.98 3.5C4.98 4.88 3.87 6 2.5 6S0 4.88 0 3.5 1.12 1 2.5 1 4.98 2.12 4.98 3.5zM.22 8.98h4.56V24H.22zM8.44 8.98h4.37v2.05h.06c.61-1.15 2.11-2.36 4.34-2.36 4.64 0 5.49 3.06 5.49 7.03V24h-4.54v-6.98c0-1.66-.03-3.79-2.31-3.79-2.31 0-2.66 1.8-2.66 3.66V24H8.44z" />
                          </svg>
                        </a>
                      ) : null}
                      {member.github ? (
                        <a class="team-link-icon" href={member.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label={`GitHub profile for ${member.name}`}>
                          <svg class="icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" role="img" aria-hidden="true">
                            <path d="M12 .5C5.73.5.5 5.74.5 12.02c0 5.09 3.29 9.4 7.86 10.94.58.1.79-.25.79-.56 0-.28-.01-1.02-.02-2-3.2.69-3.88-1.54-3.88-1.54-.53-1.35-1.3-1.71-1.3-1.71-1.06-.73.08-.72.08-.72 1.17.08 1.79 1.2 1.79 1.2 1.04 1.79 2.73 1.27 3.4.97.11-.75.4-1.27.72-1.56-2.55-.29-5.24-1.28-5.24-5.71 0-1.26.45-2.29 1.19-3.1-.12-.29-.52-1.47.11-3.07 0 0 .97-.31 3.18 1.18a11.1 11.1 0 0 1 2.9-.38 11.1 11.1 0 0 1 2.93.39c2.2-1.49 3.17-1.18 3.17-1.18.63 1.59.23 2.77.11 3.06.74.81 1.18 1.84 1.18 3.1 0 4.44-2.7 5.41-5.27 5.7.41.35.77 1.04.77 2.11 0 1.53-.01 2.76-.01 3.14 0 .31.21.67.8.56A10.53 10.53 0 0 0 23.5 12C23.5 5.74 18.26.5 12 .5z" />
                          </svg>
                        </a>
                      ) : null}
          </div>
          </div>
                  <div class="team-heading">
                    <div class="team-name-row">
                      <h3>{member.name}</h3>
        </div>
                    <span class="team-role-tag">{member.role}</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <p class="team-tagline">{member.tagline}</p>
                <ul class="team-highlights">
                  {member.highlights.map((highlight) => (
                    <li>{highlight}</li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
                <button
                  type="button"
                  class="team-toggle"
                  data-bio-toggle={member.id}
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls={`bio-${member.id}`}
                  id={`toggle-${member.id}`}
                >
                  Read bio
                </button>
                <div
                  id={`bio-${member.id}`}
                  class="team-bio"
                  role="region"
                  aria-labelledby={`toggle-${member.id}`}
                  aria-hidden="true"
                  hidden
                >
                  {member.bio.map((paragraph) => (
                    <p>{paragraph}</p>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
      </section>

    <section id="engage" class="anchor-offset">
      <div class="container">
        <article class="engage-panel split-copy--framed split-copy--framed--engage">
          <header class="engage-header">
              <span class="hero-eyebrow">Suit Up or Sponsor Up</span>
            <h2>Help us protect critical infrastructure.</h2>
            <p>
              Builders, operators, and funders drive our momentum. Share your talent, pilot the pipeline, or back the mission so veteran defenders can move faster.
            </p>
          </header>
          <div class="engage-grid">
            <article class="engage-card">
              <h3>How you can engage</h3>
              <div class="contributor-grid">
                {contributorPaths.map((path) => (
                  <div class="contributor-item">
                    <h4>{path.title}</h4>
                    <p>{path.detail}</p>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="engage-card engage-card--contact">
              <h3>Contact EVR:RDY</h3>
              <p>Let’s coordinate next steps and keep critical infrastructure defended forward.</p>
              <ul class="contact-list">
                <li>
                  <strong>Email</strong>
                  <a href="mailto:founders@evrrdy.com">founders@evrrdy.com</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Operations</strong>
                  <a href="mailto:ops@evrrdy.com">ops@evrrdy.com</a>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <div class="partner-contact">
<h3>Partner briefings</h3>
